TextBody:
Hi Daniel,
Thank you for reaching out.

Please find the Microsoft MDM Intune deployment guide here:
https://helpcenter.netwrix.com/bundle/EndpointProtector_5.9.4/page/Content/EndpointProtector/Install/Agent/Intune/Overview.htm

Could you please clarify whether you are referring to the eDiscovery policies or the CAP policies when discussing scan speeds?

• CAP policies scan uploads/traffic in real time, reporting or blocking actions as defined in the policy.
• eDiscovery policies scan the entire computer or specific locations (depending on the policy configuration). The duration of the scan depends on factors such as storage size, the number of files, and the number of computers on which the policy is applied.

I hope this answers your question. If you have any further questions or concerns, please do not hesitate to contact us.
Best Regards,
Iosif Muntean| Technical Support Engineer

DLP | Device Control | Content Aware Protection | eDiscovery | Enforced Encryption
 www.endpointprotector.com

Hi Daniel,

The maximum number of records returned in a report can be set from the Device Control -> Global Settings -> scroll to the bottom of the page to the Display Settings section and select another value from the dropdown:


Regarding the eDiscovery policy scan speed, as far as I know, the EPP Server does not affect the speed of the scans, so it remains the computer performance, but just to make sure I will confirm this with the engineering team.
